author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
OnlyFans has carved a niche out of the $250 billion creator economy by welcoming adult content. The company wants to build a different kind of a social media platform – one that’s not reliant on advertising and personalized algorithms. 

WSJ sat down with CEO Keily Blair to discuss why she thinks OnlyFans can be one of the safest digital platforms out there.

0:23 Where Blair worked before OF
1:01 OF’s search function

3:18 Why OF is not on the App Store

6:56 AI threats for OF
8:56 Future challenges 
11:15 Going from a lawyer to social media CEO

title: OnlyFans CEO on Why She Isn’t Chasing an IPO, Site Design and More | WSJ
